-- Software Billionaire Nadar to Give 10% of Wealth to India Charity, ET Says
-- B y   U n n i   K r i s h n a n
-- 2010-09-29T01:44:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/software-billionaire-nadar-to-give-10-of-wealth-to-india-charity-et-says.html
Shiv Nadar, founder of Indian
software-services provider HCL Technologies Ltd., pledged to
donate 10 percent of his wealth for philanthropic ventures, the
Economic Times said, quoting him in an interview.  Nadar will donate his wealth to build and run free schools,
a proposed university, and a museum of art, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
